# Git Conventions

## Branch Naming

```
feat/entity-connections      # new feature
fix/embedding-timeout        # bug fix
refactor/service-layer       # refactoring
docs/api-schema              # documentation
test/item-generation         # adding tests
```

Always branch from `main`. Keep branches short-lived.

## Commit Messages

```
feat: add entity embedding pipeline
fix: handle null content_type in edge creation
refactor: extract repository layer from services
docs: update plan.md with data entity spec
test: add integration tests for group permissions
```

- Prefix with type: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `docs`, `test`, `chore`.
- Imperative mood, lowercase, no period at end.
- Body (optional): explain *why*, not *what*.

## Pull Requests

- One logical change per PR.
- PR description must include: summary, what changed, how to test.
- Require at least 1 team member review before merge.

## What NOT to Commit

- `.env` files or any secrets/API keys
- `__pycache__/`, `.pyc` files
- IDE-specific files not in `.cursor/rules/` (e.g., `.vscode/settings.json`)
- Large binary files or datasets
